by jrorie@....</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='36184#1521734597'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2018-03-22T16:03:17+00:00">Mar 22, 2018 04:03 PM UTC</time> by <b>clundstedt@....</b><a class="anchor" name="1521734597">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>I think you&#39;re past these points, but GOC poked me and I missed this, sorry.

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;1) To clarify, are you asking about a specific user because we&#39;re in central phedex, or is it something different? Looking in the phedex load test &#62;directory it seems uscms01, a service user account on our cluster, owns them locally.</font>
As long as the phedex cert maps to the same UNIX account that owns the /store area you&#39;re fine.  I don&#39;t know if you want all the files owned by the same user that generic cms users can map to as they&#39;d be able to erase/alter your storage  contents.  All the files at Nebraska are owned by the Unix user cmsphedex and only my cert, which operates our Phedex agents, maps to that user.

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;2) Files in /store/user are owned by the local account of the user that initiated the transfer/stage out. Files in /store/temp/user are owned by &#62;uscms01.</font>
This is all correct, but see above about uscms01 owning everything.

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;The mapping between the local account name and the DN was placed in a file named local-gridmap that was then passed into grid-&#62;mapfile.  We l&#62;ike it this way because it allows users to manage their files once they&#39;ve been staged out from CRAB jobs (read&#58; they don&#39;t have to ask &#62;a uperuser). &#62;Can we keep a similar scheme under LCMAPS?</font>

Absolutely.  Since you were using mkedg gridmap it should be easy.  Just take the generated gridmap file, strip out any automatically created mappings (so just leaving your local maps) and drop those into your new gridmap file on everything.  The vo-map should take care of the other users.

Nothing should need superuser/root.  If you bump into permission issues that are causing problems we&#39;ll need to tweak things but never root to grid users.

Cheers,
Carl

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;I think I can just create the new accounts; do any of them need root-level permissions?</font>

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;Thanks,</font>

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;Jamal</font></pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='36184#1521724581'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2018-03-22T13:16:21+00:00">Mar 22, 2018 01:16 PM UTC</time> by <b>Sarah Schmiechen</b><a class="anchor" name="1521724581">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hi Carl,

